Only possible to look into BP and BPE, DJP also has a soil moisture water measurement at 2cm height, but it is only 0 and in a few cases weve got crazy outliers.. doesnt really make sense.

Log transformation to see better what is happening with SMC: log(SMC+1) because that way 0 doesnt result in -Inf. Where SMC is 0, log(SMC+1) is 0 too. Highest measured SMC is 0.165, which translates to 0.152 log(SMC+1).

Problem:

  • Theres only T and RH at the iButton locations, and only SMC at the AWS locations.
  • iButtons: good spatial and elevational gradient coverage
  • SAWS: good accuracy, actually measuring SMC and not RH
  • RH and SMC: there seems to be some connection but no clear relationship
  • SMC and T: sometimes theres a great relation (BPE 2012) sometimes not really..
  • T and RH: there is obviously no relation between temperature and RH
